Job Description
We are seeking a Devops Engineer to join our team. This is a full-time, hybrid role primarily located in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania, with occasional remote work flexibility. The role focuses on supporting and enhancing a statewide web-based grants management system used for public safety, victim services, law enforcement, and court offices across Pennsylvania.
What You'll Do

  *   Develop and design software solutions to meet user requirements
  *   Define test plans and acceptance criteria for technical components
  *   Ensure technical solutions align with business requirements
  *   Execute detailed design and product testing
  *   Adhere to programming standards and best practices
  *   Manage and report time spent on all work activities
  *   Collaborate effectively in a team environment and communicate status updates clearly
  *   Anticipate and resolve issues specific to the team’s activities
  *   Identify, document, and track issues, risks, and action items

What You'll Need
Required:

  *   5+ years of experience developing complex applications in an object-oriented environment
  *   Proficiency in Visual Basic and C# for application development
  *   5+ years of experience working with XML, CSS, and HTML
  *   5+ Years of strong experience with SQL Server or a comparable RDBMS
  *   Familiarity with source code management tools
  *   Advanced MS Office skills

Preferred:

  *   3+ years of experience with SSRS (SQL Server Reporting Services) and SSIS (SQL Server Integration Services)
  *   Experience with issue tracking management tools
  *   Understanding of public safety, criminal justice, training and certification, or financial systems concepts
  *   Exposure to Telerik .NET UI controls



If interested Please send me your resume at hemendra.kalal@zenosys.com<mailto:hemendra.kalal@zenosys.com>
